03/12/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Security agents searched the apartments early Wednesday (December 2nd) of three people suspected of helping war crimes fugitive Ratko Mladic. 
The head of Serbia's council for co-operation with The Hague war crimes tribunal, Rasim Ljajic, told Blic on Thursday that the raids were aimed at finding "clues, evidence and materials". 
The searches were conducted in New Belgrade and in the suburbs of Bezanijska Kosa and Veliki Mokri Lug. 
(Blic, Vecernje Novosti, B92, Reuters - 03/12/09)
